From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 06:44:46 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/sysfs-schemes: delete tried region in
 regions_rmdirs()

The issue was discovered [1] by Sashiko.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260513011920.119183-1-sj@kernel.org

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/sysfs-schemes.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/sysfs-schemes.c b/mm/damon/sysfs-schemes.c
index 20d50388f0e28..93d4bfc302ba3 100644
--- a/mm/damon/sysfs-schemes.c
+++ b/mm/damon/sysfs-schemes.c
@@ -257,7 +257,6 @@ static void damon_sysfs_scheme_region_release(struct kobject *kobj)
 	struct damon_sysfs_scheme_region *region = container_of(kobj,
 			struct damon_sysfs_scheme_region, kobj);
 
-	list_del(&region->list);
 	kfree(region);
 }
 
@@ -335,6 +334,7 @@ static void damon_sysfs_scheme_regions_rm_dirs(
 	list_for_each_entry_safe(r, next, &regions->regions_list, list) {
 		/* release function deletes it from the list */
 		damos_sysfs_region_rm_dirs(r);
+		list_del(&r->list);
 		kobject_put(&r->kobj);
 		regions->nr_regions--;
 	}
-- 
2.47.3

